issue.title: performance audit on main page and about
issue.body:
feat: Refactor OfficeStructure component for performance and mobile layout

This commit introduces a series of refactorings to the `OfficeStructure` component to improve code organization, boost performance, and fix several mobile layout issues identified during a performance audit.

Key changes include:

- **Code Splitting**: The large `OfficeStructure.js` component has been broken down into three smaller, more focused components:
  - `departmentNav.js`: Handles the department selection sidebar.
  - `departmentDetails.js`: Manages the display of department-specific information (header, sub-departments, responsibilities).
  - `reportingStructure.js`: Renders the organizational chart.

- **Data Abstraction**: The `organizationStructure` data object has been moved to a dedicated file (`officeStructureData.js`), centralizing content and separating it from component logic. The deprecated crown emoji icon has also been removed as requested.

- **Mobile Layout Fixes**:
  - The main container cards are now properly centered on mobile viewports, preventing them from flushing against the right border.
  - The sub-departments and key responsibilities containers now have equal spacing on both sides for improved visual appeal.
  - The reporting structure cards have been enhanced with a single-column layout on smaller screens to prevent text overflow and improve readability.
  - The `next/image` component syntax was updated to use modern props, replacing the deprecated `objectFit` prop with the `style` attribute to prevent warnings and ensure optimal image rendering performance.

These changes lead to a cleaner, more maintainable codebase and a significantly better user experience on mobile devices.

issue.body:
This PR implements a configurable "manual translation timing" feature that can be enabled per-target to perform OCR and translation only on the first user-initiated capture, skipping processing for subsequent frames until capture is restarted.

## Changes Made

### Settings Integration
- **TargetSettings.cs**: Added `IsManualTranslationTiming` boolean property with default value `false`
- **AllSettingsViewModel.cs**: Added UI property for the setting in the "Misc" category
- **Settings saving/loading**: Integrated the new setting into the save/load workflow

### UI Enhancement
- **PropertyGrid**: New checkbox appears in Target-specific Settings under "ãã®ä»–" (Misc) section
- **Localization**: Added translations for all supported languages:
  - æ—¥æœ¬èªž: "ç¿»è¨³ã‚¿ã‚¤ãƒŸãƒ³ã‚°ã®æ‰‹å‹•åŒ–ã‚’æœ‰åŠ¹ã«ã™ã‚‹"
  - English: "Enable manual translation timing" 
  - Deutsch: "Manuelle Ãœbersetzungszeit aktivieren"
  - í•œêµ­ì–´: "ìˆ˜ë™ ë²ˆì—­ íƒ€ì´ë° í™œì„±í™”"
  - And more for Vietnamese, Chinese (Simplified/Traditional)

### Core Logic Updates
- **MainViewModelBase.cs**: Modified to read the setting and only apply first-capture-only behavior when enabled
- **Conditional processing**: OCR and translation skipping only occurs when the setting is explicitly enabled
- **Event handling**: CaptureStarted event resets the flag only when the feature is active

## Behavior

**When disabled (default):**
- Application works normally, processing all frames
- No change in existing behavior

**When enabled:**
1. First user-initiated frame triggers OCR and translation processing
2. Subsequent frames are skipped until capture is restarted
3. Processing load is reduced significantly after initial recognition

**Per-target configuration:**
- Each translation target can have this setting configured independently
- Setting is saved in user configuration and persists across application restarts

This implementation provides the requested functionality as a configurable option rather than hardcoded behavior, allowing users to choose when to enable the performance optimization through manual control of translation timing.

Fixes #428.
